<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Receives Draft of UN Sanctions From U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo Receives Draft of UN Sanctions From U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1506125894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1250 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1506125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 15 KYODO -- Japan has received a draft 
resolution the United States plans to submit to the UN Security 
council to impose sanctions on North Korea for its suspected 
nuclear arms development program, a chief government spokesman 
said Wednesday. 
  The proposed sanctions "are in no way easygoing," Chief 
Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai said without elaboration. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

