<H3> <TI>   Working-Level Talks on Procurement Scheduled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Working-Level Talks on Procurement Scheduled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1506075194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0725 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1506075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 15 KYODO -- Japan and the United States 
will hold working group meetings on bilateral trade "Framework" 
talks in Tokyo later this week and next week to discuss 
government procurement areas, the Foreign Ministry announced 
Wednesday [15 June]. 
  The working group meeting on telecommunications equipment 
will be held Thursday and Friday, and the meeting on medical 
equipment will be held June 22 and 23, both in Tokyo, the 
ministry said. 
  Ministry sources have said vice ministerial-level meetings 
on 
the Framework talks between Deputy U.S. Trade Representative 
Charlene Barshefsky and Deputy Foreign Minister Sadayuki Hayashi 
will be held June 22 and 23 in Tokyo. 
  Barshefsky is expected to arrive in Japan on June 21, the 
sources said. 
  Japan and the U.S. agreed in May to restart the Framework 
talks after reaching common ground on the definition of 
objective criteria that it would be both quantitative and 
qualitative yardsticks instead of numerical targets for each of 
the negotiation sectors. 
  Government procurement of medical and telecommunications 
equipment is one of the three priority areas along with 
automobile and auto parts, and insurance business. 

</TEXT>

