<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
told Japanese business leaders Tuesday [14 Jun] his government 
is willing to allow self-service gas stations in Japan on 
certain conditions, as part of deregulation, government 
officials said. 
  Hata was responding to a proposal by Isao Nakauchi, vice 
chairman of the Federation of Economic Organizations 
(Keidanren), that self-service gas stations be introduced in 
