also asked Hata for his leadership in implementing deregulation. 
  Keidanren executives handed a petition to Hata, asking him 
to 
cut the number of economic regulations in half over the next 
five years, and map out a plan for scrapping and privatizing 
government-backed corporations as well as consolidating 
government departments. 

