<H3> <TI>   WPK Secretary Meets Japanese Farmers Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    WPK Secretary Meets Japanese Farmers Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1306054594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0445 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306054594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 13 (KCNA) -- Hwang Chang-yop, 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of 
Korea, Sunday met and had a friendly talk with the delegation of 
the Japan-Korea Friendship Exchange Association of Agricultural 
Farmers headed by Masao Yoshida, former Social-Democratic member 
of the house of representatives of Japan and chairman of the 
association. 
  The head of the delegation said that during his stay in 
Korea 
he witnessed the achievements made by the Korean people in 
socialist construction under the banner of the chuche idea, 
closely rallied around the great leader His Excellency President 
Kim Il-song and the dear leader His Excellency Kim Chong-il. 
  Noting that Korea has made great achievements in agriculture 
by implementing the rural theses, he said he saw the peaceful 
looks of farmers of the northern half of Korea engaged in 
farming even in areas near the Military Demarcation Line. 
  He said he got a good knowledge of the progress of socialist 
construction in Korea, seeing the splendid apartment houses of 
Tongil street built under the wise guidance of the dear leader 
His Excellency Kim Chong-il. 

</TEXT>

