<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam Orders Security Briefings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Yong-sam Orders Security Briefings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506031094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0302 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506031094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 15 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam on 
Wednesday instructed the Foreign and Defense Ministries to 
provide daily press briefings on day-to-day changes in major 
international issues and the nation's security situation. 
  Kim ordered the daily briefings in view of the need to 
alleviate the people's sense of insecurity amid growing 
uncertainty over the nation's security, Presidential Press 
Secretary Chu Ton-sik said. 
  In accordance with the instructions, the Foreign Ministry 
will conduct press briefings on developments in the nuclear and 
other issues at the United Nations, as well as other major 
international affairs, while the Defense Ministry will brief the 
media on the military situation in North Korea and the nation's 
defense preparedness, Chu said. 

</TEXT>

