<H3> <TI>   SDPJ Mission Leaves Pyongyang, Returns Home </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ Mission Leaves Pyongyang, Returns Home </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1406150294 Tokyo KYODO in English 1453 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1406150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- A three-member delegation 
of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) [Social Democratic Party of 
Japan (SDPJ)] to North Korea returned to Japan Tuesday [14 June] 
night from a four-day visit to Pyongyang. 
  During its stay in Pyongyang, the delegation, led by House 
of 
Representatives member Kozo Watanabe of the second largest 
opposition party, exchanged views over the suspected nuclear 
arms development program with officials of the North Korea's 
workers' party. 
  North Korea told the delegation that the country is not 
trying to develop nuclear weapons, according to SDP officials. 
  The SDP delegation told the North Korean side that the SDP 
wants a peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue through talks. 

