<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 15 June Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On the prospect of UN disciplinary measures 
regarding the DPRK's (North Korea) announcement to secede from 
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), Foreign Minister 
Koji Kakizawa said at the 14 June House of Councilors' Budget 
Committee meeting: "I think it will be economic sanctions." He 
then said: "Some people have an apprehension that the phased and 
gradual measures, which we proposed, may be shortened. We hope 
that North Korea will understand the international community's 
stance and will not launch hasty countermeasures." He made 
these remarks in a response to a question by Fujio Saito of the 
Liberal Democratic Party. 

</TEXT>

