<F P=101> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Cuba-Vietnam Construction Company Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Cuba-Vietnam Construction Company Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1506043694 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0724 GMT 14 Jun 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1506043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" Item] </F>
  [Text] Hanoi, 14 Jun (UNA-ECOPOOL) -- The mixed 
Vietnamese-Cuban VIC Construction Company has been constituted 
here. Cuban Deputy Construction Minister Alfonso Llamas will 
chair the administrative council and Vietnamese Dr. Nguyen 
Truong Tien will be the company director. 
  VIC's total capital is estimated at $6.6 million, out of 
which $2.2 million are legal funds provided by the two parties 
in equal shares. 
  The VIC Construction Company inauguration, which is the 
first 
joint venture [previous two words in English] between the two 
countries, was attended by Vietnamese and Cuban Ministers Nguyen 
Cong Tan and Arturo Guzman, who are co-presidents of the 
Vietnamese-Cuban Committee for Economic and Science and 
Technology Cooperation. 
  The company will be based in Hanoi and will have branches in 
Haiphong and Ho Chi Minh City. It's activities include bids for 
construction projects, advisory services, production and 
commerce of construction materials, among others. 

</TEXT>

