<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundtables for National Reconciliation Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundtables for National Reconciliation Held </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    KR Refuses Proposed Schedule </H4>

<F P=102> BK1506123094 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1506123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The meeting of the commission on the roundtable for 
national reconciliation and peace in Cambodia was held 
energetically at Damnak Chan Pavilion in the Royal Palace. 
  His Excellency [H.E.] Ung Teaseam, under secretary of state 
for information, told national and international correspondents 
at the end of this first meeting that the participants discussed 
the first issue, that is, a cease-fire. Regarding this issue, 
the representatives of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] 
and National Assembly followed His Majesty's idea. To speed up 
a concrete schedule for the cease-fire, the RGC representatives 
proposed a starting date of 30 June or earlier. 
  Meanwhile, the Khmer Rouge [KR] side proposed that a control 
committee be set up and still refused to accept the proposed 
schedule. 
  The roundtable meeting adjourned at 1200 and will resume 
work 
tomorrow morning at 0900. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

