<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] 'Ala'eddin Borujerdi, deputy foreign minister for 
Asian-Pacific affairs, met ambassadors from North Korea and 
South Korea in separate meetings today. Borujerdi noted the 
Islamic Republic of Iran's profound concern over increasing 
tension in the Korean peninsula. Borujerdi emphasized that 
Tehran believes direct talks between the two Koreas are the best 
way to solve current problems. 
  The North Korean envoy said that American actions are the 
main cause of problems between the two Koreas. The envoy 
stressed that North Korean officials are ready to solve problems 
of the two Koreas through negotiations. 
  The South Korean envoy stated Seoul's readiness to solve 
existing problems between the two Koreas via direct 
negotiations. The South Korean envoy said that the Islamic 
Republic of Iran, through its good relations with the two 
Koreas, can play an effective role in reducing tension between 
the two Koreas. 

</TEXT>

