  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 9 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- At the 
closed sitting of the Mongolian parliament the legislators have 
discussed and approved the proposal of the Mongolbank on issuing 
new 5 and 10 thousand bank notes as well as new coins of 20, 50, 
100 and 200 tugrug of value. The central bank is substantiating 
the necessity for such a step by the growing rates in the 
prices, wage, pensions and allowances. The coins supposed to 
issue are to be serving as a means of fare payment in the public 
transport or applying in slot-machines for rendering small 
services. 

