<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Firm To Fly New Routes to Singapore, Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Firm To Fly New Routes to Singapore, Kazakhstan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1206121294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1027 GMT 11 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1206121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 11 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian civil aviation "Miat" company has set new air route 
flights to Kazakhstan and Singapore. 
  The air flights on the route to Almaty from Ulaanbaatar with 
a stop-off in the Bayanulgii in the western part of the country 
where are residing mainly Mongolian Kazakhs, are to be 
functioning every Thursday. 
  What about Singapore, the Miat is to perform charter flights 
in accordance with the agreement concluded between the Mongolian 
State Tourist "Juulchin" company and Singapore's tourist 
"Universal Travellers" company. 

</TEXT>

