<H3> <TI>   National Assembly Proceedings Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Assembly Proceedings Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ministers Answer Questions </H4>

<F P=102> BK1606104694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1606104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by station correspondent on 15 Jun proceedings of </F>
the current Ninth National Assembly's fifth session in Hanoi] 
  [Summary] "Dear friends: the Ninth National Assembly's 
fifth session entered its 18th work day today. The National 
Assembly held a plenary session at the conference hall under the 
direction of National Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh to hear 
ministers answer questions put forth by various deputies." 
  In the morning session, the National Assembly heard Tran 
Dinh 
Hoan, minister of Labor, War Invalids and Social Welfare answer 
questions related to pensions for retired cadres, allowances for 
wounded soldiers, and wage scales for cadres of education and 
medical agencies at the grass-roots level. They also heard 
Construction Minister Ngo Xuan Loc answer questions concerning 
the prices of houses in Ho Chi Minh City and other provinces, 
and Trade Minister Le Van Triet answer questions related to the 
import of papers, motorcycles, and cars. 
  "In the afternoon session, the National Assembly heard Dau 
Ngoc Xuan, minister and chairman of the State Commission for 
Cooperation and Investment, answer questions on granting 
licenses to foreign investors and the results of joint ventures 
during the past period. They also heard Phan Ngoc Tuong, 
minister and chairman of the Government's Cadre Organization 
Committee, answer questions on issues related to the 
implementation of government decree no. 46 on the policy toward 
village cadres at grassroots units during the past year, the 
assignment of cadres to villages and wards, and issues related 
to the illegal import of cars in Song Be, Tay Ninh, and Dong Nai 
provinces. 
  "At the same session, Tran Hoan, minister of Culture and 
Information answered questions on the current cultural 
activities and management of cultural publications and artistic 
shows." 
  Tomorrow, 16 June, the National Assembly will continue its 
work at the conference hall. 

</TEXT>

