<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Evans Warns DPRK To Reconsider Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Evans Warns DPRK To Reconsider Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1606062894 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1606062894 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia says the international community may have 
no choice but to take stronger action against North Korea 
following its decision to withdraw from the International Atomic 
Energy Agency [IAEA]. Camille Funnell reports in a statement 
issued from New York Australia's foreign minister, Senator 
Evans, called on North Korea to reconsider its decision: 
  [Begin Funnell recording] Senator Evans said uncertainty 
about the nature of North Korea's nuclear activity is the cause 
of instability in the Asia-Pacific region, and he said it 
undermines the interest of all countries in the region in 
preventing the spread of nuclear weapons. Senator Evans warned 
the international community will have little choice but to take 
stronger action, including through the United Nations Security 
Council, if North Korea does not display a more constructive 
position. He said it is in everyone's interest, not the least 
to North Korea, to reconsider its decision and return to the 
negotiating table. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

