<H4>    Kumagai Negative on U.S.-DPRK Talks </H4>

<F P=102> OW1606081794 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 15 Jun 94 
Evening Edition p 4 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1606081794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is speculated that talks may possibly be held 
between the United states and the DPRK (North Korea) around late 
June on DPRK's suspected nuclear development. Regarding this 
speculation, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai indicated 
his negative view at a news conference held on the morning of 15 
June, and said: "Judging from the developments so far and the 
U.S. position, it is difficult to imagine that such talks will 
be held unless DPRK meets the demands of the international 
community." 

</TEXT>

