<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diet To Pass Budget 22 Jun at `Earliest' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diet To Pass Budget 22 Jun at `Earliest' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1506055894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0532 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1506055894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 15 KYODO -- The Diet will pass the 
long- overdue state budget for fiscal 1994, which started April 
1, next Wednesday [22 June] at the earliest, Diet sources said 
Wednesday. 
  A leading member of the House of Councillors Budget 
Committee, Masakuni Murakami of the opposition Liberal 
Democratic Party (LDP), proposed in talks with Juro Saito, head 
of LDP upper house members, Tuesday night that the upper house 
pass the budget next Wednesday "for the sake of the people," the 
sources said. 
  But Saito reportedly said he considered June 27 an 
"appropriate" date to pass the delayed budget. 
  According to the sources, LDP chief Yohei Kono, Secretary 
General Yoshiro Mori, Saito, Murakami and other members of the 
party's upper house executives will meet Thursday to decide 
their budget strategy. 
  On June 8 the House of Representatives approved the 73.08 
trillion yen budget for fiscal 1994. The current Diet session 
ends June 29. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-29197 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas116_a_94014" </HT>


<HEADER>
