<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata Receives Petition on New Electoral System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Receives Petition on New Electoral System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1506054794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0359 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1506054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 15 KYODO -- A senior Liberal Democratic 
Party (LDP) member presented Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata on 
Wednesday [15 June] with a petition calling for the next general 
election to be held under the new electoral system approved by 
the Diet earlier this year. 
  The petition was signed by LDP lawmaker Yuji Tsushima and 
305 
other House of Representatives legislators, or more than half of 
the 511 lower house members. 
  The new electoral system combining 300 single-seat 
constituencies and 200 proportional representation seats has yet 
to be implemented pending passage of a bill defining the 
electoral districts. 
  Hata told Tsushima and other petitioners that he fully 
agrees 
with the thrust of their petition, officials said. 
  He called on proponents of the new electoral system to work 
together in their respective capacities to see it realized. 
  Tsushima, deputy chairman of the LDP's Policy Affairs 
Research Council, paid calls later in the day on leaders of the 
Social Democratic Party, New Party Sakigake, the Democratic 
Socialist Party and Komeito, as well as lower house Speaker 
Takako Doi. 

</TEXT>

