<H3> <TI>   U.S. Steps Against Peace Treaty Proposal Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Steps Against Peace Treaty Proposal Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606105994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1050 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Foolish Ruse To Mislead Public Opinion'--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- MINJU CHOSON in a 
commentary today denounces the United States which, displeased 
with the proposal and step of the DPRK for the establishment of 
a new peace arrangement, is alleging that the latter wrecked the 
Korean armistice agreement. 
  The analyst says: 
  The United States, far from accepting the DPRK's just 
proposal for ensuring peace on the Korean peninsula, is crying 
over "the violation of the armistice agreement", taking issue 
with it. This is intended to cover up its crimes in having 
deliberately and systematically destroyed the Korean armistice 
agreement and armistice machine and shift the blame on to the 
other. 
  It is the United States that destroyed and scrapped the 
Korean Armistice Agreement. After it was signed in July 1953, 
the United States, a signatory to it, began violating it even 
before the ink on the agreement was dry. 
  The U.S. side had shipped new types of weapons including 
nuclear weapons into South Korea in secrecy by camouflaged 
method, afraid of the Korean Armistic Agreement in the past 
days. But now it is introducing and deploying them openly in 
broad daylight. 
  In March 1991 it was the United States that appointed a 
"general" of the South Korean army without legal authority or 
qualification in view of the Korean Armistice Agreement "senior 
member" of the U.S. side, thus incapacitating the armistice 
machine from fulfilling its function. 
  The U.S side's attempt to revive the armistice machine is 
intended to persist in war provocation moves and keep tensions 
on the Korean peninsula. 
  The United States will be well advised to act with 
discretion, mindful that its perfidious act is not favourable to 
it. 

</TEXT>

