<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-U.S. Protests by ROK Students Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606052394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606052394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Anti-U.S. Struggle of South Korean Youth" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- South Korean youth and 
students waged anti-U.S. struggles in front of the "American 
Cultural Centres" in Taegu and Pusan, Seoul-based radio reports 
said. 
  Young people in Taegu Tuesday scattered copies of literature 
denouncing the United States for screwing up the situation of 
the Korean peninsula with nuclear pressure on the North, 
shouting anti- American slogans and pouring paint on the 
building of the "American cultural centre" in the city and a 
police post. 
  They accused the United States of driving South Korean 
agriculture into bankruptcy with pressure to open agricultural 
product market. 
  On the 15th, students under the Pusan-South Kyongsang 
Provincial Federation of General Student Councils staged a 
surprise demonstration in front of the "American Cultural 
Centre" in Pusan. 
  They occupied a road and condemned the United States for 
creating a war crisis, shouting "objection to the U.S. 
heightening tensions on the Korean peninsula" and other slogans. 
  In a statement they charged that the U.S. harms the peaceful 
atmosphere of the Korean peninsula, clamouring for 'sanctions' 
against the North with the approach of the 3rd round of North 
Korea- U.S. talks. 

</TEXT>

