<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Remarks by ROK Student Group Leader Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0430 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Hanchongnyon Chairman Denounces Kim Yong-sam 'Regime' as </F>
Flunkeyist and Treacherous One" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 15 (KCNA) -- Student Kim Hyon-chun, 
chairman of the second-term of the Federation of General Student 
Councils of South Korea, in an interview with HANGYORE SINMUN 
denounced the Kim Yong-sam "regime" as a flunkeyist and 
treacherous one. 
  In his interview he said it was proved that the present 
"regime" is a treacherous and flunkeyist "regime" which evaded a 
probe into the May 18 truth and opened rice market against the 
demand of the people over the last one year and coiled up 
tensions on the Korean peninsula with the introduction of 
Patriot missiles. 
  It is a judgement of Hanchongnyon that there is no need to 
expect from the Kim Yong-sam "regime" any longer, he said. 
  Touching on this year's reunification movement, he said that 
the federation would defend the principle of great national 
unity, demand the signing of a peace agreement and continue to 
maintain the keynote of the student movement in the 
reunification movement including a successful opening of the 
pan-national rally. 
  He demanded that the present "regime" renounce its 
anti-reunification attitude to suppress Hanchongnyon. 

</TEXT>

