<H3> <TI>   Pomchonghaknyon Statement on Japanese `Suppression' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pomchonghaknyon Statement on Japanese `Suppression' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506051394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506051394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 15 (KCNA) -- A spokesman of the 
North side headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and 
Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghaknyon) 
issued a statement to the press Tuesday denouncing the Japanese 
authorities' suppression of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans in Japan. 
  He said that the raid on the Kyoto prefectural headquarters 
of Chongnyon by the Japanese police on June 6 was a downright 
expression of the Japanese authorities' heinous hostile policy 
toward the DPRK in collusion with the United States and the 
South Korean puppets. 
  The Japanese authorities are escalating crackdown on 
Chongnyon, talking about study of "measure for public peace at 
home" and establishment of "emergency security arrangements" he 
said, adding: 
  If the Japanese reactionaries think they can go scotfree 
after provoking Chongnyon, a dignified overseas citizens' 
organisation of the DPRK, and Koreans in Japan with a futile 
design to realize the old dream of "greater East Asia 
coprosperity sphere", it would be a big mistake. 
  The Japanese authorities must ponder over the consequences 
of 
their anti-DPRK and anti-Chongnyon racket, immediately give up 
such moves and sincerely apologize for all the criminal acts 
they have committed up to now and punish the criminals. 
  The spokesman expressed the belief that the Korean youth and 
students at home and abroad under Pomchonghaknyon would actively 
turn out in a struggle to defend the democratic national rights 
of the Korean youth in Japan, our brothers and sisters, and the 
dignity of the homeland from the Japanese reactionaries' ever 
intensified fascist suppression. 

</TEXT>

