<F P=103> SK1606114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
of the Korean Christians Federation in a statement Wednesday 
said that the surprise raid and forcible search of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and its 
officials by the Japanese police, part of the hostile policy 
toward the DPRK, is a deliberate and premeditatedicrime to 
destroy Chongnyon organisation and block its patriotic 
activities. 
  It strongly demanded that the Japanese authorities 
immediately stop their hostile policy toward the DPRK and 
anti-Chongnyon campaign, strictly punish those who are 
responsible for it and take a responsible step so as to prevent 
the suppression of the Chongnyon and infringement upon the human 
rights of Koreans in Japan. 
  The statement expressed the hope that all the Christians of 
the world who respect love and reconciliation, peace and justice 
and broad segments of the Japanese people would pay a serious 
attention to the grave obtaining situation, help stop the 
Japanese authorities' hostile policy toward the DPRK and 
anti-Chongnyon campaign and continue to express support and 
solidarity for Chongnyon in its righteous activities for 
democractic national rights and national reunification. 

