<H3> <TI>   More Criticism of `Suppression' of Chongnyon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Criticism of `Suppression' of Chongnyon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406215994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1509 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Japanese people are 
denouncing the authorities' suppression of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon). 
  Hiromi Takahashi, representative member of the Edokawa Ward 
People's Society in Tokyo, Japan, for supporting the independent 
and peaceful reunification of Korea, charged that Japan has 
defined the Democratic People's Republic of Korea as "the 
enemy," fostering tension under the pretext of its "nuclear 
issue" and suppressing Chongnyon. 
  He urged the Japanese Government to take steps to prevent 
outrages against Koreans in Japan. Lawyer Takayuki Yoshida 
denounced the search of the Kyoto prefectural headquarters of 
Chongnyon by the Japanese police and called for pooling strength 
in the struggle against "an emergency system" sought by the 
Japanese reactionary forces. 
  Takayoshi Yamanaka, vice-chairman of the All-Japan 
Federation 
of Peasants Unions, said though Japan must ask pardon of the 
Korean people for the issues of "comfort women for the Army" and 
forcible drafting, it is increasing tension in league with the 
United States and South Korea. 
  Warning that the suppression of Chongnyon today will reach 
the Japanese people tomorrow, he called for checking such 
fascist suppression. 

</TEXT>

