<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting Held To Welcome PRC School Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting Held To Welcome PRC School Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606114394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1055 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held on 
June 15 at Changdok school, Mangyongdae District, Pyongyang 
Municipality, to welcome the delegation of Jilin Yuwen Middle 
School, China. 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song conducted 
revolutionary activities, studying at Jilin Yuwen Middle School 
from January 1927 to Autumn of 1929. 
  Kang Chun-ho, principal of Changdok school said in his 
speech 
at the meeting that Jilin Yuwen Middle School with a long 
history is a proud school which actively struggled against the 
Japanese imperialist aggressors and reactionary warlords in the 
past and trained excellent revolutionaries of China in this 
course. The teachers and students of the school have better 
tended the statue of respected Comrade Kim Il-song erected at 
their school out of a noble desire to convey forever the undying 
revolutionary relics of Comrade Kim Il-song, the great leader of 
the Korean people, and develop the traditional Korea-China 
friendship down through generations, he said. 
  Zhao Zhongxin, secretary of the Party Committee of the 
school, who is heading the delegation, speaking next, referred 
to the fact that President Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il 
sent precious gifts to the school several times with deep 
concdrn. He said that they consider the school a symbol of 
China-Korea friendship. 
  The friendship between Yuwen school and Changdok school is 
all the more precious because the two schools are the historical 
places where President Kim Il-song studied. 
  Saying that Changdok school with modern educational 
equipment 
has a wealth of precious experience in instruction and 
education, he laid stress on deepening friendship between the 
two schools. 
  Souvenirs were exchanged at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

