<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK To Use Japanese Wives as `Human Shield' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK To Use Japanese Wives as `Human Shield' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606112994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1119 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 16 (YONHAP) -- North Korea plans to move 
the Japanese wives of Korean men in the North to near the 
Yongbyon nuclear estate for use as a "human shield" against 
possible attack by the United States, a leading Japanese weekly, 
SHUKAN BUNSHUN, reported in its latest June 23 issue. 
  The weekly said the Japanese wives of those Korean men 
repatriated from Japan to North Korea in the late 1950s are 
officially estimated at 1,831 but their number would actually 
run to thousands. 
  The report said it had obtained the information that some 
Japanese women in North Korea flashed an "SOS" to Japanese 
authorities, saying "we are about to be sent to an area near 
nuclear facilities." 
  "If this is true, Pyongyang apparently intends to use the 
Japanese wives as a human shield against possible U.S. attack on 
nuclear facilities," a Japanese Defense Agency official was 
quoted by the weekly as saying. 
  "This could also be a blackmail or retaliation against the 
Japanese Government moving to join international sanctions 
against North Korea over the nuclear question." 

</TEXT>

