<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Defector Accepted at Kimpo After Fleeing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Defector Accepted at Kimpo After Fleeing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606070894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0635 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 16 (YONHAP) -- A 36-year-old North 
Korean arrived at Kimpo airport Thursday, months after defecting 
to a third country to seek asylum in the South, the Agency for 
National Security Planning (NSP) said. 
  Chin Kwang-ho, born to an ethnic Korean family repatriated 
to 
the North from Japan, was working as a driver at a supply base 
in a North Korean military academy when he defected in early 
February, according to the NSP. 
  Grievances over the severe discrimination against Koreans 
repatriated to the North from Japan drove Chin to flee, the 
agency said. 
  The South Korean Government decided to accept him from a 
humanitarian point of view. 
  Chin has a mother and an elder sister still living in North 
Korea, the NSP said. 

</TEXT>

