<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia: Five N. Koreans `Unwelcome' Diplomats </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia: Five N. Koreans `Unwelcome' Diplomats </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0133 GMT 16 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1606022394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It has been revealed that the five North Koreans 
who were recently deported from Russia for attempting to obtain 
nuclear materials [haek mulchil] were diplomats. 
  (Basilev), spokesman for the Counter-Intelligence 
Headquarters of the Russian Federation, said today that the five 
North Koreans who tried to obtain materials [mulchil] for use in 
manufacturing nuclear weapons were designated as figures to be 
avoided [kipi inmul], that is, unwelcome diplomats in the 
country where they work, and were deported from Russia in the 
spring. 

</TEXT>

