<H3> <TI>   PRC Denies Rumor of DPRK Military Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Denies Rumor of DPRK Military Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606051794 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2200 GMT 16 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1606051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By YONHAP from Moscow] </F>
  [Text] Regarding our country's media reports that China 
will provide military assistance to North Korea in case a 
military collision breaks out on the Korean peninsula, a 
spokesman for the Chinese Foreign Ministry denied such reports, 
reported ITAR-TASS in a Beijing-dispatched story. 
  The Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman, in a telephone 
interview with ITAR-TASS, strongly denied such reports by saying 
that the reports are a absolutely groundless fiction [chonjoguro 
ssulttae omnun hogurago]. 
  The news agency reported that the spokesman, however, kept 
silent on reports that a close woman relative of North Korean 
President Kim Il-song visited Beijing at the end of May and 
agreed with the Chinese side to receive food and energy if 
economic sanctions are imposed on North Korea. 

</TEXT>

