<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Minister Named `Special' Ambassador </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Minister Named `Special' Ambassador </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606061394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0545 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 16 (YONHAP) -- Former Vice Foreign 
Minister Hong Sun-yong was reinstated to the ministry as special 
grade one ambassador-at-large Thursday. 
  Hong, who served as ambassador to the former Soviet Union, 
was replaced last month. He is expected to tour South America 
as South Korea's special envoy from next month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

